Ntuthuko Shoba and the Thulsie twins at the High Court in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - The murder trial of Ntuthuko Shoba continues on Thursday. On Wednesday, the High Court in Johannesburg heard that there were WhatsApp messages between Shoba and Tshegofatso Pule, revealing that they had been fighting. READ: Tshegofatso Pule | Court hears Shoba, killer met on day of murder The messages were retrieved from Shoba’s second cellphone, which the police found during his arrest. This was revealed during the cross-examination of Sergeant Mpe Teme, a detective investigating the murder. WATCH: Tshegofatso Pule Murder Trial | Expert testimony on cellphone records Shoba is on trial for ordering a hit on his pregnant girlfriend, allegedly to stop his wife from finding out about the affair. Pule’s body was found hanging from a tree on the West Rand two years ago.